records.addlTxt:
Cases 15CF95, 15CF231 and 15CM214 called together at 1:32pm [mo]
Defendant Teeghun Taylor in court with Attorney Samantha J. Humes.   ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.

ADA Shock verifies victim rights compliance in all files.

The Court grants admission of the Amended Information 

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; pleas of " No Contest " entered on Counts #1, #2, and #3 of the Amended Information of Case 15CF95 and Counts #1 and #2 of Case 15CM214; factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts the pleas, finds Defendant guilty as to each offense, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Joint Motion of the Parties, the Court reads-in and dismisses: Case 15CF231

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel

On Case 15CF95 Counts #1, 2, and 3 of the Amended Information and Case 15CM214, the Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 3 years, with conditions:

--On 15CF95 count #1: to serve 20 days in the Jefferson County Jail, with Huber/work-release privileges, to commence on  10/1 /15 at 6:00pm.
--to undergo assessment, treatment or counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program as approved by the Agent
--On Case 15CF95 Count #1: to pay costs of $243 plus the $200 DNA surcharge

--On Case 15CF95 Count #2: to pay costs of $243 plus the $200 DNA surcharge
--On Case 15CF95 Count #3: to pay costs of $243 plus the $200 DNA surcharge
--On Case 15CM214 Count #1: to pay costs of $243 plus the $200 DNA surcharge
--On Case 15CM214 Count #2: to pay costs of $243 plus the $200 DNA surcharge
--to pay restitution to Dennis Holterman in the amount of $500 joint and several with co-Defendants
--to pay 10% restitution processing fee

As to Case 15CF95: Days credit for time already served:  1  day
As to Case 15CM214: Days credit for time already served:  2  days
recess:2:06pm
